# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Golden Years RN Management System
# Environment Variable Template
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# INSTRUCTIONS:
#   1. Copy this file and rename the copy to:  .env.local
#   2. Fill in your real values in .env.local
#   3. NEVER commit .env.local — it is blocked by .gitignore
#   4. This file (env.example) IS safe to commit
#      because it contains only placeholder values
#
# HOW TO COPY:
#   Mac / Linux terminal:  cp env.example .env.local
#   Windows terminal:      copy env.example .env.local
#
# WHERE TO FIND YOUR REAL VALUES:
#   Supabase Dashboard → Settings → API
#   https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/YOUR_PROJECT/settings/api
#
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════


# ── SUPABASE ──────────────────────────────────────

# Your Supabase project URL
# Example: https://abcdefghijklmnop.supabase.co
SUPA_URL=__SUPA_URL__

# Your Supabase anon / public key
# This is the "anon public" key — NOT the service_role key
# The service_role key must never appear in any frontend file
SUPA_KEY=__SUPA_KEY__


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Add future API keys below using the same pattern.
# Use a placeholder value here, real value in .env.local
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Example — SendGrid email notifications:
# SENDGRID_API_KEY=__SENDGRID_API_KEY__

# Example — Twilio SMS alerts:
# TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=__TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID__
# TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=__TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN__
